# arvo. Architecture Design

> Numeric primitives + analysis algorithms with Hot / Warm / Cold /
> Precise strategy markers. `#![no_std]`, no alloc. Zero dependency
> on platform. Extracted from polka-dots / hilavitkutin consolidation
> so all consumers (hilavitkutin, loimu, saalis, clause-dev's
> language stack, polka-dots) share one substrate.

## Principles

1. **Strategy-parameterised primitives.** Numeric containers declared
   at type level as `Hot` / `Warm` / `Cold` / `Precise`, driving
   storage width and codegen choices without runtime dispatch.
2. **no_std, no alloc.** The entire substrate is const-sized.
   Consumers pre-allocate; arvo never calls into an allocator.
3. **Trait contracts, not concrete types.** Sub-crates generic over
   trait bounds so downstream code picks its own concrete
   instantiations. Trait declarations live in dedicated contract
   crates (small transitive dependency footprint per consumer).
4. **Monomorphisation is the dispatch.** No `dyn`, no `TypeId`. The
   monomorphised function IS the type identity.
5. **Const-trait-driven.** Per round 202604271346, every trait whose
   methods are sensibly callable in const context is `pub const trait`
   (RFC 3762 line). Trait projections work in const fn bodies; default
   bodies stay reachable from const generic positions.

